on POS; Figure 5b LOA","Source Page(s)":"7, 11","Notes":"Disease-area benchmark from 14 major disease groupings plus All indications."},"source_ids":["pos_workbook:source-based-pos-workbook-xlsx"],"missing_data_flags":[],"confidence":0.9},"pricing":{"annual_wac":3341.0,"wac_value":3341.0,"wac_unit_basis":"package","matched_product":"NUPLAZID Oral Capsule 34 MG 30","dosing_summary":"2 DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION Recommended dose is 34 mg taken orally once daily, without titration. ( 2.1 ) Can be taken with or without food. ( 2.2 ) Capsules may be swallowed whole or opened and entire contents sprinkled over a tablespoon of certain types of soft food. ( 2.2 ) 2.1 Recommended Dosage The recommended dose of NUPLAZID is 34 mg taken orally once daily, without titration. 2.2 Administration Information NUPLAZID can be taken with or without food [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3) ] . NUPLAZID capsules can be taken whole, or opened and the entire contents sprinkled over a tablespoon (15 mL) of applesauce, yogurt, pudding, or a liquid nutritional supplement. Consume the drug/food mixture immediately without chewing; do not store for future use. 2.3 Dosage Modifications for Concomitant Use with CYP3A4 Inhibitors and Inducers Coadministration with Strong CYP3A4 Inhibitors The recommended dose of NUPLAZID when coadministered with strong CYP3A4 inhibitors is 10 mg, taken orally as one tablet once daily [see Drug Interactions (7.1) ]. Coadministration with Strong or Moderate CYP3A4 Inducers Avoid concomitant use of strong or moderate CYP3A4 inducers with NUPLAZID [see Drug Interactions (7.1) ] .","source_ids":["wac:california-wac-data-xlsx","openfda_label:pimavanserin-34-mg"],"missing_data_flags":[],"confidence":0.8},"commercial_model":{"calculable":true,"annual_patients":1000.0,"peak_penetration":0.2,"gross_to_net":0.15,"net_price":2839.85,"peak_net_sales":567970.0,"revenue_forecast":[{"year":1,"treated_patients":20.0,"net_price":2839.85,"net_revenue":56797.0},{"year":2,"treated_patie